21/08/2007
ATHENS, Greece -- Officials rounded up 63 illegal immigrants Monday (August 20th) in various parts of country. 
In one case, a 16-year-old boy was discovered hiding in a vehicle, loaded aboard a ferry headed out of Greece. 
Another 18 people, including women and children, were caught on Samos island, as was a separate group of 41 illegal immigrants from Lebanon, Somalia and Afghanistan.
Also Monday, Greek police arrested a father and a son for allegedly trafficking illegal immigrants. 
They were detained on the road between Florina and Edessa while transporting a group of nine people. 
(NET TV, ERT - 20/08/07)
